==Filmography==
In addition to its own library, Universal releases the EMKA, Ltd. catalog of 1929–1949 Paramount Pictures, owned by sister company Universal Television.

===Film series===
===Highest-grossing films===
Universal was the first studio to have released three billion-dollar films in one year; this distinction was achieved in 2015 with &quot;Furious 7&quot;, &quot;Jurassic World&quot;, and &quot;Minions&quot;.


‡ Includes theatrical reissue(s).

